.TH "__ssp_update_baud_rate" 9 "__ssp_update_baud_rate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__ssp_update_baud_rate \- set the UART "baud rate"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __ssp_update_baud_rate
.BI "(struct sifive_serial_port *ssp "  ","
.BI "unsigned int rate "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ssp" 12
pointer to a struct sifive_serial_port
.IP "rate" 12
new target bit rate
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calculate the UART divisor value for the target bit rate \fIrate\fP for the
SiFive UART described by \fIssp\fP and program it into the UART.  There may
be some error between the target bit rate and the actual bit rate implemented
by the UART due to clock ratio granularity.
